==Starting the quest==
===Talking to Veliaf Hurtz===
* {{topt|If continuing from [[In Aid of the Myreque]]}}
** '''Player:''' So what now?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Well I'd say our mission to establish a new hideout has been a great success. All thanks to you, of course.
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{topt|If coming back to Veliaf}}
** '''Player:''' Hello again. How's things?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Very good. I'd say our mission to establish a new hideout has been a great success. All thanks to you, of course.
** {{tact|continue}}
* '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' With the hideout sorted, we can now start focusing on the vampyres again. We're looking to re-establish contact with the Sanguinesti region.
* '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' I also want to look into a diplomatic mission into Misthalin. The support of the king would be very helpful in our fight against Drakan.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Is there something I can do to help out?}}
** '''Player:''' Is there something I can do to help out?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Well, we could use some help with scouting a route into the Sanguinesti region. Are you interested in learning more details?
** {{tselect|Start the Darkness of Hallowvale quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes. Please tell me more.
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' There should be another group of Myreque working in the Sanguinesti region. We need to re-establish contact with them. To do that, we need a route into the region.
*** '''Player:''' How do I get into the Sanguinesti region?
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' The entire region is surrounded by a wall that you'll find impossible to get over.
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' That said, you might be able to find a way around the wall at the point where it meets the sea. Perhaps there's something in Burgh de Rott that could help you.
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Once you're in, try and establish contact with the Myreque there. I'm sure they'll have sympathisers amongst the citizens. Someone should be able to point you in the right direction.
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' One last thing to be aware of is the vyrewatch. They're powerful vampyres that patrol the entire region. We haven't found any way of killing them. Even the Rod of Ivandis does nothing!
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|Can you tell me more about the Sanguinesti region?}}
**** '''Player:''' Can you tell me about the Sanguinesti region?
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' It's a large region to the east of here. The southern part is a city called Meiyerditch. Humans live there in ghettos and are regularly tithed by the vampyres.
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' The northern part is the vampyre capital of Darkmeyer. It is from his castle there that Lowerniel Drakan rules over all of Morytania.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|How do I get into the Sanguinesti region?}}
***** '''Player:''' How do I get into the Sanguinesti region?
***** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' The entire region is surrounded by a wall that you'll find impossible to get over.
***** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' That said, you might be able to find a way around the wall at the point where it meets the sea. Perhaps there's something in Burgh de Rott that could help you.
***** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Once you're in, try and establish contact with the Myreque there. I'm sure they'll have sympathisers amongst the citizens. Someone should be able to point you in the right direction.
***** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' One last thing to be aware of is the vyrewatch. They're powerful vampyres that patrol the entire region. We haven't found any way of killing them. Even the Rod of Ivandis does nothing!
***** {{tact|previous2}}
**** {{topt|Can you tell me more about the Sanguinesti Myreque?}}
***** {{tact|below}}
**** {{topt|Okay, thanks.}}
***** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Can you tell me more about the Sanguinesti Myreque?}}
**** '''Player:''' Can you tell me more about the Sanguinesti Myreque?
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Certainly. The Myreque, or at least the resistance that has now become the Myreque, originated in the region. Previously there was nothing.
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' It was many years ago that a small group, led by a man called Safalaan Hallow, managed to escape from the ghettos of Meiyerditch.
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' They got information out about what was happening and helped to organise the resistance, which today is called the Myreque.
**** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' The name was given to us by the locals, who named us after the place where we hid in Mort Myre.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|How do I get into the Sanguinesti region?}}
***** {{tact|above}}
**** {{topt|Can you tell me more about the Sanguinesti region?}}
***** {{tact|above}}
**** {{topt|Okay, thanks.}}
***** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Okay, thanks.}}
**** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
**** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' Err, no thanks.
*** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Very well. We'll be here if you change your mind.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What will you do here in Burgh de Rott?}}
** '''Player:''' What will you do here in Burgh de Rott?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Oh, the usual. Keep a low profile and keep an eye on what the vampyres are up to. There's also plenty of research to do with all the new information you've found for us.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Why re-establish contact with the Sanguinesti region?}}
** '''Player:''' Why re-establish contact with the Sanguinesti region?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' The region is where the heaviest blood tithing takes place. It's also home to some of the more senior members of vampyre society, including Lowerniel Drakan himself.
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' Assuming the vampyres haven't put an end to them, there should be another group of Myreque operating in the region. We will need  their support in the fight against the vampyres.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Why ask Misthalin for some help?}}
** '''Player:''' Why ask Misthalin for some help?
** '''Veliaf Hurtz:''' We can't hope to fight the power of the vampyres alone. We'll need help from Misthalin by the bucket-load if we're to stand a chance against them.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Okay, thanks.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
** {{tact|end}}

